### PAGE 4: Team / Employee Management (`/employees`)

**Purpose:** Manage team members shown on the website's About/Team page.

#### Employee List View

**Top Section:**
- Page title: "Team Members"
- "Add Team Member" button (top-right)
- Toggle view: Active / Inactive / All

**Display:** Card grid (3 per row on desktop, 1 on mobile)

**Each Card Shows:**
- Profile image (or initials placeholder if no image)
- Name (bold)
- Position (e.g., "Full Stack Developer")
- Department badge
- Active/Inactive status indicator (green/gray dot)
- Order index number (small, top-right corner)
- Action buttons: Edit, Toggle Active, Delete

**Alternative:** Can also be a table view with sortable columns.

#### Create/Edit Employee Modal or Page

**Form Fields:**
- **Name** — Text input (required)
- **Position** — Text input (required, e.g., "CEO", "CTO", "Full Stack Developer")
- **Department** — Text input or dropdown ("Engineering", "Design", "Management", "Marketing")
- **Bio** — Textarea (short biography)
- **Profile Image** — Image upload with preview
- **LinkedIn URL** — Text input (URL validation)
- **Order Index** — Number input (determines display ordering on website; lower = first)
- **Active** — Toggle switch (if inactive, not shown on website)

**Bonus Feature: Drag & Drop Reordering**
Allow admin to drag-and-drop team members to reorder them instead of manually entering order numbers.

**API Calls:**
```
GET    /api/employees              ← List all (admin sees all including inactive)
GET    /api/employees/:id          ← Get single employee
POST   /api/employees              ← Create employee
PATCH  /api/employees/:id          ← Update employee
DELETE /api/employees/:id          ← Delete employee
POST   /api/upload/image           ← Upload profile image
```

